<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Vice Consul at
                                    Foochow</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The right of consular asylum is not claimed by this Government, but you
                            may use your discretion as to granting temporary refuge where such is
                            necessary to preserve innocent human life, carefully avoiding action
                            that might appear partisan.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>